images.name: Mariota [600x600]
images.caption: Marcus Mariota ran five times for 56 yards, including a 5-yard TD run, above, early in the fourth quarter.

articles.description: With the Commanders opting to sit Jayden Daniels in the second half due to leg soreness, Marcus Mariota came on and threw a 5-yard touchdown pass to Terry McLaurin with two seconds remaining to give Washington a 23-19 win over the Cowboys.
articles.headline: Commanders win late again, this time behind Marcus Mariota

images.name: McCarthy Cowboys Commanders_250105 [1296x729]
images.alt: Cowboys coach Mike McCarthy and his staff are out of contract at the end of the NFL season.
images.caption: Cowboys coach Mike McCarthy and his staff are out of contract at the end of the NFL season.

articles.description: ARLINGTON, Texas -- The Dallas Cowboys' season came to an end with a 23-19 loss to the Washington Commanders Sunday, and now comes the challenging part.
articles.headline: Cowboys' Jones praises McCarthy, won't commit to future role

images.name: Broncos rout Chiefs to clinch playoff berth
images.caption: The Broncos defeat the Chiefs 38-0 in Week 18 to secure a spot in the playoffs, setting up a matchup with the Bills in the wild-card round.

articles.description: The Broncos defeat the Chiefs 38-0 in Week 18 to secure a spot in the playoffs, setting up a matchup with the Bills in the wild-card round.
articles.headline: Broncos rout Chiefs to clinch playoff berth

images.name: 250105 Young [1296x729]
images.caption: Bryce Young had a career day against the Falcons on Sunday, becoming just the third quarterback in Panthers history to account for five touchdowns in a game. He also posted a career-best 123.5 passer rating.

images.name: Bryce Young's 5th TD of the day restores Panthers' lead
images.caption: Bryce Young takes it himself and scores a 10-yard rushing touchdown to give the Panthers a 38-31 lead in the fourth quarter vs. the Falcons.

articles.description: Dave Canales has committed to QB Bryce Young being the Panthers' starter for 2025, allowing him to focus on a defense that set a record for points allowed in a season.
articles.headline: Panthers commit to Bryce Young as starting quarterback for 2025

images.name: Commanders beat the Cowboys on last-gasp Terry McLaurin TD
images.caption: Marcus Mariota finds Terry McLaurin in the back of the end zone for a go-ahead Commanders touchdown.

articles.description: — Jayden Daniels sitting in the second half wasn’t the plan when the playoff-bound Washington Commanders visited the Dallas Cowboys with only seeding at stake.
articles.headline: Mariota leads playoff-bound Commanders to 23-19 win over Cowboys after replacing Daniels

images.name: Bryce Canales [608x342]
images.caption: Panthers coach Dave Canales refused to commit to Bryce Young as the starting quarterback for the remainder of the season until Week 16.

images.name: Panthers' Miles Sanders scores the game-winning TD in OT
images.caption: Miles Sanders scores a rushing touchdown in overtime to give the Panthers a 44-38 win over the Falcons.

articles.description: Baltimore Ravens' Michael Pierce had a simple explanation for why he took a knee after his interception, among other top Week 18 comments.
articles.headline: Canales' quip on Panthers' unfortunate accomplishment leads Week 18 post-win quotes
